New York state's politicians have been accused of leaving most major legislative business unfinished this year.
But they did accomplish one thing that will have far-reaching implications for young daredevils: passing a law requiring that children under 14 wear safety helmets while riding skateboards in public areas.
This is many skateboard riders practice dangerous stunts and flips on flat surfaces or walls.
Pataki's action means that New York has joined other states a center of skateboarding in the country, in requiring helmets.
